      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be computed for all QoIs across at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI on hemolysis index must be below 5%.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted and GCI values were computed for pressure rise and flow uniformity. Discretization error on the hemolysis index itself remains at approximately 9% GCI due to sensitivity of the power-law damage model to local shear stress gradients in the impeller region. The team notes this is within typical ranges reported in the open literature for rotating machinery hemolysis simulations and considers the overall discretization characterization sufficient for regulatory submission."
    },
