      "acceptanceCriteria": "A documented use-error assessment must identify potential analyst errors in model setup, boundary condition specification, and post-processing, with controls demonstrated for each identified risk.",
      "rationale": "The modeling team followed established internal simulation guidelines and applied standard boundary condition templates for rotating machinery. Peer review of the simulation setup was performed by a senior analyst. General good practice in CFD workflow management provides confidence that operator-induced errors are unlikely to have materially affected results."
